	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You need a bit of active hardware to do it. Something that watches the bus and then plays with the !CARTIN signal to prevent bus fights with MegaCD side when the BIOS area is accessed. If you can disable the BIOS chip in the MCD you will not have to deal with any active logic and run ROM from cart directly (and leave the !CARTIN open).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


